          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 08</h1><p><strong>Questions 11 - 15</strong></p><p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A, B or C</strong>.</p><p>11 Which statement is true of the Chelston Hall eating arrangements?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Students can eat somewhere else, but they must still pay for the meals that are provided.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Students can only eat at Chelston Hall, as it is a service they have paid for.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Students do not have to eat at Chelston Hall and do not have to pay for the service.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>12 When is breakfast served on Saturday?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    7.00 a.m. - 8.30 a.m.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    7.00 a.m. - 9.30 a.m.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    8.00 a.m. - 9.30 a.m.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>13 What should students do when they finish their meals?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Leave their plates on the table.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Put their plates on the sidetable.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Tell the staff politely that they have finished.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>14 What will be stopped if the students do not use it respectfully?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    The tea and coffee service.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Access to the TV room.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Access to the laundry room.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>15 What type of coin do the washing machines take?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    A one-pound coin</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    A fifty-pence coin</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    A twenty-pence coin</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table>",
